        <num>CCP 1432</num>
        <heading>1432.  Use of deposition</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1432.  Use of deposition
A deposition to perpetuate testimony taken under Articles 1429 through 1431 may be used in any action involving the same subject matter subsequently brought in any court of this state, in accordance with the provisions of Article 1450.</p>
        </content>
